07/12/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- A total of six bilateral co-operation agreements were sealed during Russian President Vladimir Putin's historic visit to Turkey, which ended on Monday (6 December). 
The countries agreed to boost co-operation in trade, the economy, the military and defence, and fighting terrorism. 
Putin and Turkish counterpart Ahmet Necdet Sezer also signed a declaration pledging that Moscow and Ankara would support each other within international institutions, including the UN. 
(NTV - 06/12/04)
